  <datafield tag="500" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
    <subfield code="a">Mary Weston gives an account of her own health and the health of Priscilla Weston and Phebe Weston. She mentions Wendell Phillips&apos;s lecture in Weymouth. Mary Weston heard that William Lloyd Garrison is at Plymouth, where there was difficulty in getting him a place where he could make his speech. Mary Weston writes: &quot;That apostate [Robert Bernard] Hall would not read the notice of his meeting, &amp; has come out a Colonizationist, ...&quot; Mary Weston comments that &quot;there was ever such a nest of vipers&quot; in the Boston Female Anti-Slavery Society.</subfield>
